info.headline: High Wind Warning issued October 28 at 12:26PM AKDT until October 29 at 1:00PM AKDT by NWS Anchorage AK
info.description:
* WHAT...East winds 45 to 55 mph with gusts up to 75 mph expected.
* WHERE...Kodiak Island.
* WHEN...From 4 AM to 1 PM AKDT Wednesday.
* IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property, and cause power outages. Travel will be difficult.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A strong low and its front moves north into the Gulf of Alaska Wednesday morning, bringing strong easterly winds across Kodiak Island through early Wednesday afternoon. Winds peak late Wednesday morning and diminish through the evening. The strongest winds will be along the eastern coast and areas susceptible to easterly channeled winds. Moderate to heavy rain will also accompany the front with rainfall totals of 1 to 2 inches likely. Higher elevations could see locally greater rainfall amounts.
info.instruction: People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown around or damaged by the wind. Prepare for the possibility of widespread power outages. Use caution if you must drive.
